d 'XTREC': module to implement Panel unit root test based on recursive detrending (Westerlund 2015)
d
d      xtrec performs a panel unit root test based on recursively
d detrended data as proposed by Westerlund    (2015, Journal of
d Econometrics). Two test statistics are available:	   t-REC:
d the baseline test assuming iid errors. Asymptotically distributed
d as N(0,1) under the		 null hypothesis of a unit root,
d regardless of the degree of the fitted trend polynomial.	   
d   This invariance property is unique among all panel unit root
d tests and eliminates the need 	   for any mean or variance
d correction factors.	     t-RREC: the robust version (invoked
d with the robust option) that accommodates serial	     
d correlation, cross-section dependence (via a common factor
d structure), and cross-section 	   heteroskedasticity. Its
d null distribution is also N(0,1), and the invariance property    
d	 extends to general trend functions beyond polynomials
d (including smooth transition shifts		 and trigonometric
d functions). 
d
d KW: time series
d KW: panel data
d KW: unit root test
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260304
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
